\int_0^\infty \frac{2x}{a}e^{\Large\frac{-x^2}{a}}\ dx=1 
u=\dfrac{x^2}{a}\;\Rightarrow\;du=\dfrac{2x}{a}\ dx
 \int_0^\infty e^{-u}\ du=1. 
\int_{0}^\infty e^{-ax^2} \, \mathrm dx = \sqrt{\pi}/2a
