xdx = d(\frac{x^2}{2})
E[Y]=\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{y}{\sigma}\sqrt{\frac{2}{\pi}}exp(-\frac{y}{2\sigma^{2}})dy=\sigma\sqrt{\frac{2}{\pi}}
\int_{0}^{\infty} y~exp(-\frac{y}{2\sigma^{2}})dy=\sigma^{2}
\int_{0}^{\infty}2 \frac{y}{\sigma^{2}}exp(-\frac{y}{2\sigma^{2}})dy=1,
\sigma^{2}=\frac{1}{2}
